-- BMW Considers Assembly Plant in Slovakia, Hospodarske Reports
-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 2012-05-02T07:18:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/bmw-considers-assembly-plant-in-slovakia-hospodarske-reports.html
Bayerische Motoren Werke AG (BMW)  is
considering options to build a car-assembly plant in Slovakia,
Hospodarske Noviny reported, without saying where it got the
information.  The German carmaker is choosing between the eastern part of
Slovakia and Mexico as the location for the factory, the
newspaper said. The plant will produce electric cars and the
company is asking the Slovak government for state aid,
Hospodarske said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
